Really loved their signature Bangkok beef noodles! I originally wanted their new spicy seafood soup but they were all sold out. I asked for this one to be spicy and they gave me a small jar of their homemade sauce so I could adjust it to my liking. The broth is fragrant and lightly sweet so I really enjoyed having it both sweet and spicy. I recommend asking for if you really like adding some heat to your meals!

A hidden gem of Logan Square. I’ve been here twice and the noodles and sushi were great each time. Had a group of 10 there last week for my birthday and they were very accommodating last minute! Everybody loved their food and the staff is all really nice.

Food was great ordered vegetarian items. Highly recommend for vegetarians looking for great food. Ordered the veggie spring rolls, edamame, veggie fried sushi and veggie ramen.  Everything was fresh and delicious and can’t wait to visit it again.

I came here during a weekday night and although it wasn't packed, it was surprisingly busy. The smell of curry hits you as soon as you walk in and it is glorious. From their menu they seem to have some sort of identity crisis because although they claim that they're a Thai restaurant, their menu is heavily inspired by Japanese food. They definitely have their Thai staples, but it seems to me that it's more of a Japanese restaurant with some Thai influence. Regardless, the food itself is delicious. We had crispy calamari and the shrimp fireball for appetizers and both of those were fantastic. I followed that up with the spicy udon noodles and told them to make it extra spicy. When it came out it, it was delicious and although it was definitely spicy, it wasn't anything I couldn't handle (I do like a lot of spice though). Overall a great little place. Would come back.

The novelty of Trike is it's menu that touts Thai dishes as well as a commendable list of sushi. The environment is contemporarily styled and comfortable and wasn't too packed even on the Saturday night that I went. From there, everything feels a bit muted. Appetizers are typical in their offerings but hardly memorable in flavor. The same goes for the noodles and sushi that I tried. No option to choose your spice level when ordering which is a bit dissapointing. It's  perfectly adequate but unlikely to leave a lasting impression.

An excellent spot! Prices are almost as outstanding as the food is fresh and delicious! The service is always really quick here. For eat-in or takeout. It is usually busy but never so busy that you're waiting for a table. The atmosphere is really enjoyable. Good music, not too loud, good app/drink selection, great for a casual or nice dinner. Food is authentic and delicious. Wide selection from Thai noodle dishes to sushi. Portions are good sized but, hard to have leftovers because it's so good. Not quite two servings more like 1.5 unless you're very hungry. Not very spicy dishes but, you can always ask for more! Really a great deal to get pad Thai and a Thai iced tea/coffee for $14. A lot more reasonably priced than a lot of nearby spots and never too long of a wait. Plus the Staff is really friendly and accommodating. Definitely worth checking out!

Last minute sushi/Thai find in Logan's Square. He wanted Thai, I wanted sushi. Bingo-Bango! This place was BYOB, delicious and cheap. I couldn't have asked for more in a last minute, unplanned dinner find. Trike managed to excel at both cuisines. If in the area, I'd definitely come back!

Another good sushi spot on Milwaukee with excellent vegan sushi options. The prices are good, the vibe is cozy and intimate, and the service is good. They have a bunch of creative rolls, and that includes fantastic vegan sushi creations. Frequently the specials include vegan items as well. Definitely a nice date spot, you can get your food, see a movie at the Logan, then hang out at the Eagle.

Good place in Logan Square for Thai food. I got the crab rangoon, miso soup, and the pad thai, to see how they did the basic stuff. They did it pretty well. The service was friendly and the food came out really fast. Maybe not as great as the N Western Thai places, this place is pretty good and convenient.

Great new addition to the logan square restaurant community. The food tasted incredibly fresh and the spices and flavors created were great. They have a fairly unique menu, omitting some standard thai fare for more interesting creations. Looking forward to trying the sushi menu soon.
